Etymology: Named in honour of the late Werner Hanagarth, zoologist, geographer, all-round ecologist of the old school, who dedicated his life's efforts to nature and people in South America , first project coordinator of SOLOBIOMA (obituary in
Beck & Höfer 2003
).

Description: Living specimens 5–7 mm long, ca. 0.2 µm wide, whitish opaque under top light. Slow body movements. Preserved specimens 4.5–7 mm long, 0.14–0.2 mm wide. Segment number mostly 32–43 (N= 26 ;
13 specimens
with 38–42 segments), rarely below 30 ( 13–24 , N= 4 , partly with regenerated posterior end).
